      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "NIH and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the regulatory QoIs specified in FDA guidance for CPB device submissions. CFD-predicted shear stress distributions are the mechanistic intermediate quantity; Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model maps shear stress to NIH. QoI chain is fully traceable to clinical endpoint.",
