      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as the COU device. Operating points span the declared envelope (1.5–6.5 L/min, 1500–3500 RPM). Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) used for bench tests; acknowledged as a limitation with documented hematocrit correction factor. Sparse coverage at low-flow extreme (single replicate at 1.5 L/min) documented as gap; engineering judgment supports adequacy at MRL 2.",
